                       Terms and Conditions

  1. Definition of "Use for Profit"

     Any activities that involve, directly or indirectly, the subject of the
     activity gaining financial benefits or any benefits in any other form that
     have the same effects as financial benefits, shall be considered
     "Use for Profit".
     "Use for Profit" includes but is not limited to:

     Directly selling anything for benefits, including but not limited to
     financial payment, gifts, partnerships, and/or services.

     Using anything to endorse or promote activities that involve benefits or
     objects related to such activities, including but not limited to
     endorsing or promoting business activities, business products, payed
     services, and/or brands.


  2. Definition of "Non-profit Use"

     "Non-profit Use" shall be considered the opposite of "Use for Profit".
     "Non-profit Use" activities do not involve any financial benefits or
     any benefits in any other form that have the same effects as financial
     benefits to the subject of the activities.
     "Non-profit Use" includes but is not limited to:

     Using anything for any personal purpose, including learning, or solving
     personal problems.

     Using anything for free and open-source software, that is, software that
     is licensed under a license approved by the Open Source Initiative at
     <https://opensource.org>.


